# Task 1: Nmap Labs Replication

## Overview
This folder contains the full walkthrough of the Nmap network scanning labs
conducted as part of the ParoCyber Ethical Hacking course. All scans were
performed on Kali Linux using Nmap 7.95 on 7 May 2026, targeting localhost
(127.0.0.1), the local 10.0.2.0/24 subnet, and the authorised external
target scanme.nmap.org.

---

## Environment
| Component | Details |
|-----------|---------|
| Attacker OS | Kali Linux (root@kali) |
| Nmap Version | 7.95 |
| Local IP | 10.0.2.15 (eth0) |
| Subnet Scanned | 10.0.2.0/24 |
| External Target | scanme.nmap.org (45.33.32.156) |
| Date | 7 May 2026 |

---

## Labs Covered

### 1. Host Discovery — `ip address`
Identified the Kali machine's own IP address before scanning.
```bash
ip address
```
**Result:** eth0 → 10.0.2.15/24

---

### 2. Basic Default Scan
Scans the top 1,000 TCP ports with default settings.
```bash
nmap 127.0.0.1
```
**Result:** All 1,000 ports closed. Completed in 0.10s.

---

### 3. SYN Stealth Scan
Half-open scan — does not complete the TCP handshake. Harder to detect in logs.
```bash
nmap -sS 127.0.0.1
```
**Result:** All 1,000 ports closed. Completed in 0.11s.

---

### 4. Full Port Scan
Scans all 65,535 TCP ports instead of the default top 1,000.
```bash
nmap -p- 127.0.0.1
```
**Result:** All 65,535 ports closed. Completed in 0.60s.

---

### 5. Aggressive Scan — Localhost
Enables OS detection, version detection, default NSE scripts, and traceroute.
`-T4` uses aggressive timing for faster results.
```bash
nmap -A -T4 127.0.0.1
```
**Result:** No open ports. OS detection returned "Too many fingerprints match."
Network Distance: 0 hops.

---

### 6. OS Detection Only
```bash
nmap -O 127.0.0.1
```
**Result:** OS detection performed — insufficient open/closed ports to give
a specific result.

---

### 7. Aggressive Scan — Local Subnet
Scans all 256 addresses in the network to discover live hosts.
```bash
nmap -A -T4 10.0.2.0/24
```
**Result:** 3 hosts found in 26.81 seconds:
| Host | Open Ports | Notes |
|------|-----------|-------|
| 10.0.2.2 | 135 (MSRPC), 445 (SMB) | Windows — SMB signing enabled |
| 10.0.2.3 | 53 (DNS) | dnsmasq 2.71 — VirtualBox gateway |
| 10.0.2.15 | None | Our own Kali machine |

---

### 8. Scan Type Comparison
```bash
nmap -sT 127.0.0.1   # TCP Connect — full handshake
nmap -sW 127.0.0.1   # Window scan — analyses TCP window size
nmap -sA 127.0.0.1   # ACK scan — maps firewall rules
nmap -sM 127.0.0.1   # Maimon scan — FIN/ACK probe
```
| Flag | Type | Result |
|------|------|--------|
| -sT | TCP Connect | 1000 closed (conn-refused) |
| -sW | Window | 1000 closed (reset) |
| -sA | ACK | 1000 unfiltered (no firewall detected) |
| -sM | Maimon | Completed — OS-dependent behaviour |

---

### 9. External Scan — scanme.nmap.org
Nmap's official authorised test server.
```bash
nmap -A -T4 scanme.nmap.org
```
**Result:**
| Port | Service | Version |
|------|---------|---------|
| 22/tcp | SSH | OpenSSH 6.6.1p1 Ubuntu |
| 80/tcp | HTTP | Apache httpd 2.4.7 |
| 9929/tcp | nping-echo | Nping Echo |
| 31337/tcp | tcpwrapped | Unknown |

---

### 10. Version Detection
```bash
nmap -sV 10.0.2.15
```
**Result:** No services detected — Kali machine has no active listeners.

---

## Key Takeaways
- Nmap covers everything from basic host discovery to OS fingerprinting in
  a single tool.
- `-p-` must be used to find services on non-standard ports.
- The `-A` flag is powerful but noisy — use slower timing (`-T1`/`-T2`)
  when stealth matters.
- ACK scans (`-sA`) reveal firewall presence even when port state is unclear.
- Always get written permission before scanning any network you do not own.

